There is a Springboot application that receives the parameters (what, where) of the route (Apache Camel) and the schedule for its execution (Quartz).
For example, log a message every second, or send a message to the ActiceMQ queue once.
A database is used to save and restore the schedule in case of an application restart.

How to correctly save and restore Apache Camel route parameters on application restart by linking it to its corresponding schedule?

```
public class CustomRouter extends RouteBuilder {

    private final int repeatInterval;
    private final String message;
    private final String destination;
    private final String triggerName;

    public CustomRouter(
            int repeatInterval, 
            String message, 
            String destination, 
            String triggerName) {
        this.repeatInterval = repeatInterval;
        this.message = message;
        this.destination = destination;
        this.triggerName = triggerName;
    }

    @Override
    public void configure() throws Exception {
        from(&quot;customQuartz://&quot; 
                + triggerName + &quot;?trigger.repeatInterval=&quot; + repeatInterval)
                .setBody(simple(this.message))
                .to(destination);
    }
}
```

