You asked for,
&gt; Unzipping 7z files with password.

One practice to so is to use [Apache Compress Library][1], i recommand to use [try, catch with-resources][2] statement to automatically close streams.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;


    public static void unzip(File file, String password) throws IOException {
        try (SevenZFile sevenZFile = new SevenZFile(file, password.getBytes())) {
            SevenZArchiveEntry archive = null;
            while ((archive = sevenZFile.getNextEntry()) != null) {
                if (archive.isDirectory()) continue;
                File outputFile = new File(archive.getName());
                try (OutputStream outputStream = new FileOutputStream(outputFile)) {
                    sevenZFile.transferTo(outputStream);
                }
            }
        }
    }


Finally i used `transferTo()` method of the `SevenZFile` object to copy the contents of the entry directly to the output stream, instead of reading and writing the contents byte-by-byte, its more efficient and faster,

  [1]: https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-compress/
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/exceptions/tryResourceClose.html

